cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.DB 

The paper proposes a method to enhance privacy-preserving logistic regression by stacking, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning for improving predicting performance. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with the problem of differential privacy, which falls under the sub-category cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The proposed method involves partitioning the data either by samples or features, which relates to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to a real application of cross-organizational diabetes prediction, which falls under the sub-category cs.DB (Databases).
